@theequalizer2557 Fair assessment. I tend not to argue much in retrospect. I often pitch a concept, analogous tangent, and then try to wrangle that back in to get my point across.

Spose I was more so offering perspective of someone who attempted and fell out of love with the craft of screenwriting when it came to the character design and execution that Ironheart has attempted.

In regards to the conversation, I do think that I remained relatively on topic in the beginning of each reply, but I do love to ramble off topic to somehow connect the dots between a concept that is a relatively new theoretical dive (such as a the specfic character design and creative choices to this show) to a concept far more practiced to my mind (much like a conversation between friends about character imitation/enaction within TTRPG's).

@Rtp4k   We don't hate anything.  We actually like Marvel and want good Marvel movies.  What we are doing is not being drone NPCs.  We objectively call out bad media and things that hurt an IP that we like. Marvel, Star Wars, Star Trek,...

Here is the thing... you are being MORE racist by liking media ONLY due to the skin color of the Protagonist.  We are actually treating everyone equally by calling out bad Movies/T.V. Shows no matter the color of the Protagonist's skin.

You are confessing through projection I am thinking.  With that in mind and using your logic... maybe you should just admit that you like a project ONLY because of the IP name and because you are racist.

@sandman_says_runrunner4701 Funny how people claim they’re being “objective” and just want good media, but Ironheart was getting review bombed and torn apart before it even released. How are you calling something bad when you haven’t even seen it yet? That’s not being objective that’s bias, plain and simple.

This video is full of microaggressions too subtle digs masked as “critique” that clearly target the show because of who’s starring in it, not the actual content.

Calling people “racist” just for liking a character of color is wild. That’s not treating everyone equally, that’s just projecting your own insecurities and hiding behind fake logic. If you’re really about good media, critique the writing, the pacing, the story not the cast’s skin color.

@sandman_says_runrunner4701 You just wrote a whole essay dripping with projection, then claimed you’re not projecting. No one’s calling the show great because the lead is Black you’re the one hyper focused on that. And if someone likes the show and points out how hate campaigns target shows like this, that’s not “mental gymnastics”, that’s media literacy.

Your “new account” conspiracy theory has been used every time something doesn’t fit your narrative. And let’s not pretend studio owned review platforms are dumping bad reviews but mysteriously leaving thousands of one star rage posts untouched.

Also, calling people ‘snowflakes’ while crying about ‘microaggressions’ shows you’re just mad people see through your bias. If the show’s not for you, cool. But stop acting like your dislike is some noble crusade for writing quality it’s not.

