@Shadypooh "Cause being THIS bothered by a superhero tv show showcasing black skin is ridiculous" - says the person arguing with many people in a thread on a single comment by OP.

"You don’t get to fight for a better world then gatekeep how the next generation continues that fight" - the only one gatekeeping is you, gatekeeping "blackness" and how black people express themselves.  If black people want to lament how black people are portrayed in media, it doesn't make them any less valid.  It's a difference of opinion.  For you claim that modern struggles equal what black people had to endure in the 60, 70s and 80s, is frankly ridiculous.  Can you tell me which rights black people don't have that everyone else has today?  What needs to change in your eyes?

You are the one being overly dramatic, performative and emotive over a TV show.  Others are just lamenting how it perpetuates negative stereotypes of black people and modern women.
